      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Multi-site observational hemolysis index validation result",
      "description": "Hemolysis index predictions from the CFD model were compared against relative hemolysis index (RHI) values collected across 12 clinical sites operating FDA generic centrifugal blood pumps. Agreement within 8% across all five flow-speed combinations was demonstrated. The observational dataset spans a wide range of operating conditions and patient physiologies, providing broad coverage that the assessment team considers representative of worst-case CPB scenarios. Statistical concordance (Pearson r = 0.94) and Bland-Altman limits of agreement (±0.06 RHI units) are reported. This evidence base is cited as primary validation support for the hemolysis prediction model.",
