      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-verification-req",
      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Hemolysis model verification requirement — controlled experiment",
      "description": "Per the device submission plan and ASME V&V 40 Section 6, hemolysis predictions must be verified against in vitro bench data generated under controlled experimental conditions. The required verification method is a controlled experiment in which independent variables (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) are systematically varied under laboratory control, with confounders held constant, to isolate model prediction error. Observational clinical data, while informative for context, does not satisfy this requirement because confounding variables cannot be adequately controlled in clinical settings.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
