    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at Gradation 1 per the ASME V&V 40 factor table for MRL 2 Class II devices. The multi-site observational validation study demonstrates strong quantitative agreement (r = 0.94, mean error 5.3%) between CFD hemolysis predictions and clinical measurements across all five COU operating points. The assessment team concludes that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device.",
